						<summary>

						<p>Three sides of a mutilated slab lying near the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara.</p>						

						<p>Much damaged. Refers to a gift made in the presence of the god Viṭhala on the banks of the Tuṅgabhadra at Vijayanagara on the occasion of a lunar eclipse. Other details are lost.</p>						

